olive oil
2 potato
½ lemon
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 cucumber
1 Brown Onion
1 packet teriyaki sauce
1 tbs soy sauce
1 tbs water
1 packet pork mince
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet Crispy Shallots
2 clove garlic

• See 'air fryer tips!' (below).
• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into wedges, then place on a lined oven tray.
• Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic. Zest lemon to get a pinch, then slice into wedges. Roughly chop baby spinach leaves and cucumber. Thinly slice onion.
• In a small bowl, combine teriyaki sauce, the soy sauce, lemon zest, a squeeze of lemon juice and the water. Set aside.

Little cooks: Take charge by combining the sauces!

• When the wedges have 10 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook pork mince and onion, breaking up mince with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.

• Add garlic to the pork and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add teriyaki sauce mixture and cook until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.

• In a large bowl, combine slaw mix, cucumber, baby spinach, mayonnaise and a squeeze of lemon juice. Toss to combine. Season to taste.

Little cooks: Kids can help by combining the ingredients for the slaw.

• Divide wedges between plates and top with teriyaki pork.
• Sprinkle over crispy shallots.
• Serve with creamy slaw and any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling over the crispy shallots!